dcterms:description: EEG signals acquired from 14 subjects with paranoid schizophrenia and 14 healthy controls, collected using a multi-channel (19 channel) EEG data acquisition system. The dataset includes pre-processed EEG signals divided into non-overlapping segments for analysis.
dcterms:title: EEG dataset from the Institute of Psychiatry and Neurology in Warsaw, Poland

dcterms:description: A publicly available EEG dataset consisting of recordings from 84 subjects (39 healthy controls and 45 schizophrenia subjects) aged 11-14 years, collected using a multi-channel (16 channel) EEG system.
dcterms:title: EEG dataset from the Laboratory for Neurophysiology and Neuro-Computer Interface at Lomonosov Moscow State University
